==Swedish==

===Etymology===
Compound of ''[[handels]]'' genitive of ''[[handel]]'' "trade" + ''[[högskola]]'' "[[university college]]".

===Noun===
{{sv-noun-reg-or|handelshögskol}}

# [[school of economics]], [[school of economics and business administration]]; A [[university]] specialized in [[business]] [[administration]] and/or [[economics]].

====Hypernyms====
*[[högskola]]
*[[universitet]]

====Usage notes====
*Despite its name, a ''handelshögskola'' is a full-fledged university.

